  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Source</strong> <em>Merchant's Manifest pg. 11</em></p><h3 class=\"framing\">Statistics</h3><p><strong>Cost</strong> 10 gp <strong>Weight</strong> 2 lbs.</p><p><strong>Damage</strong> 1d4 (small), 1d6 (medium); <strong>Critical</strong> x2; <strong>Range</strong> -; <strong>Type</strong> B; <strong>Special</strong> Monk, see text</p><p><strong>Category</strong> One-Handed; <strong>Proficiency</strong> Simple</p><h3 class=\"framing\">Description</h3><p>These weapons are treated sticks of wood, either left bare or covered in elaborate decorative designs. Baston fighting sticks vary in length from 2 to 4 feet, with thicknesses varying between 1 to 3 inches. In most applications, these weapons are similar to clubs or quarterstaffs, but in the hands of a trained expert, they truly shine. A creature with the Combat Reflexes feat treats the weapon as having the blocking and performance weapon special features (<em>Pathfinder RPG Ultimate Equipment</em> 22).</p>",
